)attr default(%+_)
  _ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>_ZCMD                                                          +
+
                                 %SET+
+
%SET+will bring up a panel that allows the user to set two default values
+specific to the current repository:
+
+Configure the default push option on a Commit. This option can be over-ridden
+on the Commit panel for any individual Commit if desired.
%
+Configure a userid to be set for all PDS Members that have been Added and are
+ready to be Committed. The userid will be changed prior to the Commit process,
+including updating the ISPF statistics file that is part of the repository.
+
+The repositories z/OS dataset HLQ may be changed with the requirement that
+the number of qualifiers remain the same as the previous HLQ.
+
+Turn off, or on, prompting for file extensions when adding a partitioned
+datasets. Note that this affects ALL repositories.
+
         +Press the%Enter+key to continue your zigi tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
)PROC
 &zcont = zigihsnp
)END
